# Firebase Configuration
# Get these values from Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Your apps > SDK setup and configuration

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Go to Project Settings (gear icon)
# 4. Scroll down to "Your apps" section
# 5. Click "Add app" and choose Web (</>)
# 6. Register your app and copy the config values above
# 7. Enable Authentication > Sign-in method > Google
# 8. Enable Firestore Database > Create database
# 9. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values
# 10. Deploy the firestore.rules file to Firebase

# Security Note:
# - Never commit .env.local to version control
# - These values are safe to expose in client-side code (they're not secret)
# - Security is enforced by Firestore rules, not by hiding config values
